WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:30.883 --> 02:33.177
Une bière, s'il vous plaît.

02:52.697 --> 02:54.490
Merci.

04:38.928 --> 04:40.430
We are closed.

04:40.513 --> 04:42.265
Just a small drink.

04:48.980 --> 04:51.023
The toilets?

05:43.951 --> 05:47.705
A quick drink and then I'll leave.

05:50.708 --> 05:52.627
Why are you rushing off?

05:52.752 --> 05:55.922
- Hmm?
- I said, why are you rushing off?

05:56.005 --> 05:57.715
I don't understand.

05:59.050 --> 06:00.968
The man from Bristol called ya.

06:06.766 --> 06:09.310
- What man?
- The man in the wheelchair.

06:46.013 --> 06:48.433
What were you doing back here?

06:50.017 --> 06:51.436
Lady,

06:51.519 --> 06:55.106
I never walk into a place
I don't know how to walk out of.

06:56.315 --> 06:58.234
Then why would you get into that van?

06:58.317 --> 07:00.695
You know the reason.

08:11.265 --> 08:13.976
Make yourselves at home.

08:14.060 --> 08:16.604
You've come a long way.

08:16.687 --> 08:19.690
- Thanks for coming.
- What's the job?

08:19.816 --> 08:23.569
There's some people
who have something we require.

08:23.694 --> 08:27.115
- And we want you to get it from them.
- It involves shooting?

08:28.241 --> 08:30.785
You must be tired.

08:30.910 --> 08:33.121
We'll tell you more tomorrow.

08:39.751 --> 08:43.923
Seven fat years
and seven lean years.

08:44.006 --> 08:46.843
- That's what it says in the Bible.
- You ever kill anybody?

08:46.926 --> 08:49.470
I hurt somebody's feelings once.

08:56.060 --> 08:57.812
Don't I know you?

08:59.814 --> 09:03.359
I don't think so. I'd remember.

09:10.491 --> 09:12.368
Okay, two-hour shifts.

09:12.493 --> 09:15.204
I'll watch the front,
you guys watch the back.

09:17.457 --> 09:19.042
Merci.

09:31.888 --> 09:33.765
You awake, then?

09:35.600 --> 09:38.144
Hmm?

09:40.688 --> 09:42.565
How we doin'?

09:47.361 --> 09:48.780
Yep.

10:07.006 --> 10:08.925
You labour or management?

10:09.133 --> 10:13.179
If I was management,
I wouldn't have given you a cigarette.

10:14.889 --> 10:18.935
I am the tour guide.
Over there is the Eiffel Tower.

10:19.018 --> 10:21.771
Over here, the Louvre.
Over there, les toilettes.

10:21.896 --> 10:24.232
What do I call you?

10:24.357 --> 10:27.068
- My name is Vincent.
- Sam.

10:30.279 --> 10:34.992
As per the agreement,
your salary will be $5,000 a week

10:35.076 --> 10:37.745
with a minimum
of four weeks' work.

10:37.870 --> 10:40.248
On the successful completion
of the mission,

10:40.415 --> 10:44.252
you will each receive
a bonus of $20,000.

10:45.712 --> 10:49.799
And by the way,
my name is Deirdre.

10:49.882 --> 10:52.844
- The broad outlines of the mission are...
- Who are your principals?

10:52.969 --> 10:54.804
For you,
there's no one but myself.

10:55.012 --> 10:56.931
Huh?

10:57.014 --> 11:00.017
And what can we infer
from your charming Irish lilt?

11:00.143 --> 11:03.229
- Anything you like.
- Where's the equipment?

11:03.354 --> 11:05.898
Tell me what you need, make a list,
and give it to Vincent.

11:05.982 --> 11:09.235
- Some of the equipment's quite technical.
- If it's in Paris, I'll find it.

11:09.318 --> 11:12.822
This is what we're after.

11:12.947 --> 11:16.909
We need to take it intact from several
men who'll be intent on preventing us.

11:17.035 --> 11:19.287
- How many men?
- You American?

11:19.370 --> 11:23.207
I think the group will be between
five and eight. No more than eight.

11:23.374 --> 11:27.920
- You don't know for sure?
- Not now but I will know before the event.

11:28.004 --> 11:31.549
If you don't know,
why say between five and eight?

11:31.632 --> 11:33.551
There's two to three cars.
The group's travellin'.

11:33.634 --> 11:35.011
- They're not in Paris?
- No.

11:35.094 --> 11:36.012
Where are they?

11:36.137 --> 11:38.723
- You'll find out soon enough.
- What's in the case?

11:40.433 --> 11:43.394
Our plan, in broad strokes, is an ambush.

11:43.519 --> 11:46.064
It's to hit the car,
to take them in transit.

11:46.189 --> 11:49.942
- Transit? City? Country?
- Right now, as I said, I don't know.

11:50.026 --> 11:52.403
But we've to move very quickly.

11:52.528 --> 11:56.991
We'll start with this: Ambush
and assault on two to three vehicles,

11:57.075 --> 12:01.788
five to eight men, and our objective
is the safe retrieval of this case.

12:01.871 --> 12:05.583
Tell Vincent
what it is you'll need.

12:05.666 --> 12:10.546
What do we know about them?
Are they French? Who are they?

12:10.630 --> 12:13.966
All you need to know right now
is that they're very unpleasant.

12:14.092 --> 12:18.679
- You've done this kind of thing before?
- You know...

12:18.763 --> 12:19.847
How difficult can it be?

12:19.972 --> 12:22.100
We have no idea
how these men will be armed?

12:22.225 --> 12:24.602
It seems they'll be
very well armed, indeed.

12:24.769 --> 12:26.813
Where are we going and
how are we getting back from there?

12:26.896 --> 12:30.066
It'll be in France, and the group
will disband at the RV point.

12:30.149 --> 12:33.820
- What does she mean?
- After that, we're on our own.

12:33.903 --> 12:36.614
- It's a military term.
- That's right.

12:36.698 --> 12:38.282
Larry, tell Vincent what you'll need.

12:38.366 --> 12:43.287
Something very fast. Audi S-8.
Something that can shove.

12:43.371 --> 12:46.124
I'm going to have it for you
by the afternoon.

12:46.249 --> 12:49.919
I'll also need a nitrous system.
I've got the specs.

12:54.590 --> 12:56.968
What do you use, weapons-wise?

12:57.135 --> 12:59.345
- Hmm? - Weapons.

12:59.429 --> 13:02.515
- I'm a... I'm a weapons man.
- Weapons man.

13:02.598 --> 13:04.517
- Yeah. - Okay.

13:04.642 --> 13:08.646
They tend to settle the argument.
So what do you favour?

13:08.771 --> 13:12.358
Well, you know. It's a toolbox.
You put the tools in for the job.

13:12.483 --> 13:13.651
What?

13:13.735 --> 13:16.863
You know,
I actually favour the old 1911.

13:16.946 --> 13:20.366
.45. Old gun.

13:22.201 --> 13:24.328
It served my country well.
A long time.

13:24.454 --> 13:26.831
Your country!

13:26.956 --> 13:29.000
Not done too well, have you,
last few wars?

13:29.125 --> 13:31.502
Perhaps not, but at least
we don't go around whining about it.

13:34.172 --> 13:34.964
You ex-military?

13:35.048 --> 13:37.050
No, I got my job
through the New York Times.

13:38.634 --> 13:41.929
- Don't let him get you down.
- It don't mean nothin' to me.

13:42.013 --> 13:43.848
I say what I think.

13:43.931 --> 13:46.392
Are you ex-military?

13:46.517 --> 13:48.728
Boys at Hereford?

13:48.853 --> 13:51.522
I'm sorry, but I'd like to go backwards.
The line of retreat is...

13:51.606 --> 13:56.152
She just told you.
We meet back at the RV, disband.

13:56.277 --> 14:00.198
I understand. I'm just trying to get
a vague notion of the opposition.

14:00.323 --> 14:06.037
We're gonna cause some animosity.
How many will be coming after us?

14:06.162 --> 14:09.207
- You worried about your own skin?
- Yeah, I am.

14:09.290 --> 14:11.209
It covers my body.

14:12.627 --> 14:16.005
All your concerns will be addressed
before we leave.

14:16.130 --> 14:18.633
- Electronics and commo.
- Not more than three cars?

14:18.716 --> 14:20.134
That is our information.

14:20.343 --> 14:22.970
- Can you get me a simulator?
- What's a simulator?

14:23.054 --> 14:26.307
Gunpowder. Sound only, no lead.
Sounds like a pistol.

14:26.391 --> 14:27.975
Quite diverting.

14:28.059 --> 14:31.729
Listen, I'm also gonna need
some bigger injection jets.

14:31.813 --> 14:34.482
The Bosch is not gonna do it.
They have to be custom-made.

14:34.565 --> 14:37.568
We going north? We going south?

14:37.652 --> 14:40.905
I'd like some new clothes.

14:40.988 --> 14:43.658
- Vincent will sort you out.
- I'll take care of it.

14:50.540 --> 14:53.710
- So what brought you here?
- A fella that doesn't work so well.

14:55.044 --> 14:57.422
The man in the wheelchair?

14:58.297 --> 14:59.799
How did he get there?

14:59.882 --> 15:04.721
That was in your neck of the woods,
back in the late unpleasantness.

15:16.065 --> 15:17.400
Good reflexes.

15:18.901 --> 15:20.695
Oh, yeah.

15:21.195 --> 15:23.406
They die hard.

15:30.329 --> 15:33.958
- Interrogation.
- What?

15:34.042 --> 15:38.129
- Methods to withstand interrogation.
- You've done that?

15:38.254 --> 15:41.215
We were taught
to hold out indefinitely.

15:43.009 --> 15:46.763
- Nobody can hold out indefinitely.
- Ah, is that so?

15:46.846 --> 15:52.477
Everybody has a limit. I spent
some time in interrogation... once.

15:52.560 --> 15:54.937
- They make it hard on you?
- They don't make it easy.

15:55.271 --> 15:59.358
Yeah, it was unpleasant.
I held out as long as I could.

15:59.442 --> 16:02.153
All the stuff they tried.

16:02.236 --> 16:04.572
You just can't hold out for ever.

16:04.655 --> 16:07.367
- Impossible.
- How'd they finally get to you?

16:07.492 --> 16:10.244
- They gave me a grasshopper.
- What's a grasshopper?

16:10.370 --> 16:14.874
That's two part gin, two part brandy,
one part crème de menthe...

16:14.999 --> 16:17.043
Fuckin' smartass!

16:17.919 --> 16:20.922
- Can you find this place?
- Of course.

16:21.047 --> 16:22.965
I know it.

16:23.091 --> 16:26.094
That's where
they wanna do the exchange.

16:26.219 --> 16:28.054
You're gonna exchange for cash?

16:29.055 --> 16:33.184
- You know these people?
- My people know them.

16:33.309 --> 16:35.561
Your people have done business
with them before?

16:35.645 --> 16:38.481
Or these people
just gave your people a number?

16:49.242 --> 16:51.536
Larry.

16:55.206 --> 16:58.876
Okay. If we're gonna do it,
let's do the goddamn thing right.

17:01.754 --> 17:04.549
- Hey! - I'm busy.

17:05.800 --> 17:08.136
Okay, come on. Let's go.

17:08.261 --> 17:11.763
The answers to your questions
I'll know when I get back.

17:11.848 --> 17:14.976
- I'll go with you.
- Go with them.

17:35.246 --> 17:37.123
Who does this girl work for?

17:37.206 --> 17:41.586
Well, she works for our betters.

17:41.669 --> 17:44.881
It seems that's what
we're meant to know.

17:52.638 --> 17:55.641
Always a waiting game.

17:55.725 --> 17:59.562
- What?
- It's a waiting game.

18:02.065 --> 18:05.360
Hey, wait.
Would you not do that, please?

18:07.445 --> 18:10.531
Bad for the night vision, yeah?

18:16.704 --> 18:18.998
There they are.

19:07.296 --> 19:10.007
- You have the list?
- Yes, I have it.

19:10.133 --> 19:11.843
Give it to me.

19:15.138 --> 19:17.682
Money?

19:18.933 --> 19:21.477
Okay. You follow my lead.

19:21.602 --> 19:23.855
Just make sure you watch my back.

19:28.609 --> 19:30.319
Don't make any sudden moves.

19:30.778 --> 19:34.365
Just because we're buying guns
doesn't mean we didn't bring any.

19:34.449 --> 19:37.744
Don't worry. Everything's fine.

19:40.371 --> 19:42.999
You want to back him up?

19:46.961 --> 19:49.088
What would I profit from your death?

19:49.172 --> 19:52.633
- Well, you'd have the money.
- I have the money already.

19:54.552 --> 19:57.013
I'll watch the back.

20:01.100 --> 20:02.727
- Have you got it all?
- Oui.

20:04.562 --> 20:07.940
- You're sure?
- Ofcourse. Come and see.

20:18.242 --> 20:19.243
There it is!

20:39.222 --> 20:41.682
It's not all here.

20:43.601 --> 20:45.853
- Vincent. - What?

20:49.816 --> 20:52.527
It's not all here.

20:52.610 --> 20:54.445
- C'est tout?
- Ah, non, non, non.

20:54.612 --> 20:58.866
Le patron va contrôler I'argent.
Vous aurez le reste de la marchandise.

20:58.950 --> 21:02.995
Tiens. Il est là dans la voiture,
avec le patron.

21:03.079 --> 21:07.542
He said the rest is in the other car.
The boss wants to check the money.

21:07.625 --> 21:10.837
If he agrees, we have no problem.

21:10.920 --> 21:12.755
Here, take the car keys.

21:12.839 --> 21:15.925
Go on. Take them.

21:19.762 --> 21:21.597
Come on. Come.

21:23.182 --> 21:25.935
Okay, give me...
Give me some of the money.

21:33.109 --> 21:36.112
Give me some of the money!

21:38.072 --> 21:40.366
- Okay.
- You aren't going in there?

21:40.450 --> 21:44.620
- Yeah, I am, and so are you.
- Why am I going in there?

21:44.746 --> 21:48.750
- Why? To protect me.
- There is no protection there.

21:48.833 --> 21:52.336
If it's a come-on, we're fish in a barrel.
Why do they want you in there?

21:52.420 --> 21:54.839
- What are you, crazy?
- You know, you think too hard.

21:54.964 --> 21:58.593
Nobody ever told me that before.
But I wouldn't go in there.

22:00.303 --> 22:03.806
- What is it, Sam?
- I don't like it. Look at it.

22:05.475 --> 22:07.351
Okay, okay.

22:07.477 --> 22:09.854
Okay, let's just do it.
Let's just do it and be done, yeah?

22:10.855 --> 22:12.273
You don't wanna go in there.

22:13.816 --> 22:17.779
- I'm getting paid to go. It's that simple.
- Okay, come on. Let's go.

22:17.862 --> 22:21.491
If anything goes down,
get next to one of those guys.

22:21.574 --> 22:23.743
If there's a sniper,
he'll be afraid to shoot his own guy.

22:23.868 --> 22:25.536
- Let's go!
- All right.

22:47.683 --> 22:49.602
Stop!

22:49.685 --> 22:51.896
Stay where you are.

23:07.745 --> 23:10.373
So, everything's fine.

23:21.300 --> 23:23.344
Shit! I can't see! I can't see!

23:36.357 --> 23:38.276
Have some of this!

23:42.905 --> 23:44.490
Fuckin' arsehole!

23:49.078 --> 23:52.248
Fuckin' have some more, you bastards!

23:53.958 --> 23:55.877
Come on! Come on!

23:57.295 --> 23:59.714
Let's go!

23:59.839 --> 24:04.093
- No! You goddamn...
- Come on! Let's go!

24:17.106 --> 24:19.067
- Is anybody hurt?
- We're fine.

24:21.027 --> 24:25.823
Almost a bit of raspberry jam
back there, yeah?

24:25.907 --> 24:27.825
A bit of raspberry jam back there!

24:31.537 --> 24:35.249
Got the swag, kept the money.
Job well done.

24:35.333 --> 24:37.251
That's a fact. That is a fact.

25:02.735 --> 25:03.861
Slow down. Slow down.

25:05.947 --> 25:08.116
I think I have to stop.

25:37.019 --> 25:37.895
Thank you.

25:49.490 --> 25:51.367
Why did you take this job?

25:53.911 --> 25:55.955
My friend, I need the money.

25:57.081 --> 25:59.459
The money is here.

26:03.755 --> 26:06.924
That's what this is, you know? Money.

26:11.012 --> 26:12.930
Yeah, but who are our employers?

26:15.558 --> 26:17.435
You're right.

26:45.922 --> 26:47.799
Excuse me.

26:47.924 --> 26:50.468
Excuse me, monsieur.

26:59.268 --> 27:01.646
The Russians are bidding for the case.

27:01.729 --> 27:05.775
The case is in Nice.
They're trying to sell it to the Russians.

27:05.858 --> 27:09.153
They're staying at
the Villa Belle Mer in Nice.

27:10.279 --> 27:14.784
- The team isn't ready.
- Whatever the team is, you do it now.

27:14.867 --> 27:17.995
The Russians have decided to bid.
We need to move now.

27:18.121 --> 27:20.164
Excuse me.

27:20.373 --> 27:23.793
I have the information.
We'll be movin' very soon.

27:23.918 --> 27:25.837
It'll definitely
be in the nature of an ambush

27:25.962 --> 27:29.799
somewhere between here and here.

27:29.924 --> 27:34.345
We'll anticipate
a three-car convoy with a backup team.

27:34.429 --> 27:37.974
We will try and stop the target
before they can get away from us.

27:38.099 --> 27:40.059
- What's in the case?
- That information isn't necessary.

27:40.184 --> 27:42.186
Is it heavy? Is it explosive?

27:42.311 --> 27:44.313
Is it chained
to some unlucky bloke's wrist?

27:44.439 --> 27:46.482
- Are we gonna have to chop it off?
- All right.

27:46.566 --> 27:48.776
I don't have to let you know...

27:48.901 --> 27:52.238
Then the price has got to go up.

27:52.363 --> 27:54.198
I'll get you the case,
but the price has gotta go up.

27:54.323 --> 27:57.076
If it's gonna be amateur night,
I want $100,000. I want it up front.

27:57.160 --> 28:01.914
I want it in a bank account. I want
another $100,000 when you get the case.

28:34.197 --> 28:37.116
Okay.

28:38.368 --> 28:42.538
We've got shooters here, shooters here.

28:42.622 --> 28:44.499
I'll tell you an old trick.

28:44.624 --> 28:45.291
Hey.

28:55.009 --> 28:57.678
- What's your problem?
- Draw it again.

28:59.097 --> 29:02.350
Draw it again.
You're the ace field man. Draw it again.

29:02.475 --> 29:06.145
It's a simple diagram.
Just draw it again. Draw what you saw.

29:06.229 --> 29:10.817
Draw it again! Draw it again.

29:13.986 --> 29:17.448
Two shooters.
Car comes through here.

29:17.532 --> 29:19.534
Shooters across from each other,
kill each other dead.

29:19.659 --> 29:22.495
- Oh, my. Where'd you learn that?
- In a regiment.

29:22.620 --> 29:25.123
- What regiment was that?
- The 22nd Special Air Service.

29:25.206 --> 29:27.625
What's the colour
of the boathouse at Hereford?

29:27.709 --> 29:30.336
What's the colour
of the boathouse at Hereford?

29:30.420 --> 29:32.380
- I don't like your attitude.
- What's the colour of the boathouse...

29:32.505 --> 29:34.966
- Fuck off!
- What's... You got the gun. I'm unarmed.

29:35.091 --> 29:38.094
Do something. Go ahead.
Do something. Do something.

29:38.219 --> 29:40.138
Do something.

29:51.274 --> 29:53.818
Tell me about an ambush?
Don't tell me about an ambush!

29:53.901 --> 29:56.946
I ambushed you with a cup of coffee.

30:00.700 --> 30:03.077
You'll get your money
when we get the case.

30:03.161 --> 30:05.955
- The others, too.
- That is what I understood.

30:06.039 --> 30:07.915
Come on.
We've gotten the word. We're movin'.

30:15.298 --> 30:17.216
Put this near the front.

30:18.760 --> 30:22.096
Careful! Careful with that!

30:33.316 --> 30:36.944
So what colour
is the boathouse at Hereford?

30:37.070 --> 30:38.988
How the fuck should I know?

31:01.386 --> 31:03.304
This'll complete your compensation.

31:06.766 --> 31:09.769
Thanks for your time.
Feel free to leave when we're gone.

31:11.437 --> 31:13.314
Do I need to suggest that you forget us?

31:16.401 --> 31:18.695
Because we will not forget.

32:23.509 --> 32:27.013
- Morning.
- I see you're reviewin' our problem.

32:27.096 --> 32:29.724
Well, either you're part of the problem,
part of the solution,

32:29.807 --> 32:32.018
- or you're just part of the landscape.
- Indeed.

32:33.394 --> 32:34.645
What's in the case?

32:35.730 --> 32:38.107
Something we're paying ya for.

32:53.039 --> 32:57.293
- You and the girl are in front of the hotel.
- The name's Deirdre.

32:57.418 --> 33:00.421
Deirdre.
Wait outside the hotel for the target.

33:00.505 --> 33:02.965
He leaves the hotel for the villa,
the villa for the hotel.

33:03.091 --> 33:04.258
He activates his cellphone.

33:04.342 --> 33:06.177
How do you know
he's gonna use his cellphone?

33:06.302 --> 33:09.180
- He'll use a phone.
- How do you know?

33:09.305 --> 33:11.682
- I'm gonna call him on it.
- How do you know he'll have it with him?

33:11.808 --> 33:14.018
He's waitin' for a call.

33:14.143 --> 33:18.398
His people will call him to tell him
the location of the meet.

33:18.523 --> 33:20.400
- Okay? - Okay.

33:20.483 --> 33:23.820
The villa, the hotel, the car,
the stop light, 8 to 10 guys.

33:23.945 --> 33:25.822
How good's their...
How good's their security?

33:25.905 --> 33:28.991
- I can't tell you.
- Well, let's find out. Where are they?

33:29.075 --> 33:30.993
The last report, they were at the hotel.

33:31.119 --> 33:32.995
- The case is at the hotel?
- We presume that it is.

33:33.121 --> 33:35.873
- That's interesting.
- Why don't we do it now?

33:35.957 --> 33:39.335
- It's tempting.
