You think you can stitch me up
on your own?

01:14:41.047 --> 01:14:44.676
If you don't mind,
I'm gonna pass out.

01:15:34.350 --> 01:15:36.811
You gonna kill me?

01:15:36.894 --> 01:15:40.815
No. I'm not gonna kill ya.

01:16:08.384 --> 01:16:10.261
Why would I want to kill ya?

01:16:29.489 --> 01:16:32.450
- I gave you a job.
- I did my job.

01:16:33.618 --> 01:16:35.286
So how'd it go wrong?

01:16:35.370 --> 01:16:37.413
I thought you wanted the case.

01:16:38.623 --> 01:16:40.416
Oh, we'll get the case.

01:16:40.500 --> 01:16:43.586
We'll get the case, eh, Gregor?

01:16:45.296 --> 01:16:47.215
Don't you worry about the case.

01:16:49.676 --> 01:16:51.803
What I want's an explanation.

01:16:51.928 --> 01:16:54.639
An explanation? For what?

01:16:54.806 --> 01:16:56.766
You bollixed it up.

01:16:56.933 --> 01:16:59.894
- I bollixed it up?
- You hired him.

01:16:59.977 --> 01:17:01.896
Through your fucking contact!

01:17:07.985 --> 01:17:11.656
- You didn't do your homework.
- Why did you have to kill Larry?

01:17:11.739 --> 01:17:13.658
Oh, Larry, is it?

01:17:14.784 --> 01:17:16.661
I was clearing up your mess.

01:17:16.744 --> 01:17:19.664
My mess?
Oh, well, you take over, then.

01:17:19.789 --> 01:17:21.666
- Eh?
- But you can't, can you?

01:17:21.791 --> 01:17:23.960
It's you that's hiding, isn't it, Seamus?

01:17:24.085 --> 01:17:26.462
It's you that can't show your face.

01:17:29.132 --> 01:17:32.593
Who else thinks that?
Who you been talking to?

01:17:32.719 --> 01:17:34.929
Isn't that the reason
why I'm doing this job?

01:17:38.558 --> 01:17:40.435
You're a good girl, Deirdre.

01:17:41.811 --> 01:17:43.730
Do your job, eh?

01:17:57.452 --> 01:17:59.579
He's tough, your Yank.

01:18:00.955 --> 01:18:02.582
You're right about that.

01:18:04.834 --> 01:18:06.085
But who is he?

01:18:07.795 --> 01:18:09.630
That's not important.

01:18:10.631 --> 01:18:13.384
Didn't he work for the CIA?

01:18:14.510 --> 01:18:16.304
He used to.

01:18:17.013 --> 01:18:18.514
Not anymore?

01:18:20.099 --> 01:18:21.768
He's on the run.

01:18:23.269 --> 01:18:24.771
You're sure?

01:18:24.854 --> 01:18:29.817
I know what he can do.
I've seen him.

01:18:29.901 --> 01:18:32.403
Why would he carve himselfup
ifhe were still CIA?

01:18:32.487 --> 01:18:35.114
He makes a call and it's taken care of.

01:18:45.666 --> 01:18:47.669
And you? How are you?

01:18:56.427 --> 01:19:01.933
We need some information.
We need to find some people in Paris.

01:19:02.016 --> 01:19:03.017
Who?

01:19:03.518 --> 01:19:06.229
An Irish man and woman,

01:19:06.312 --> 01:19:08.564
a German, an ex-KGB.

01:19:09.357 --> 01:19:10.441
They're professionals.

01:19:10.566 --> 01:19:12.068
They're in hiding.

01:19:12.735 --> 01:19:15.822
This is really important to you?

01:19:18.032 --> 01:19:20.576
He saved my life.

01:19:23.454 --> 01:19:24.330
Bon.

01:19:26.749 --> 01:19:29.293
I'll find them for you.

01:19:48.062 --> 01:19:50.857
Where's the case?

01:19:54.360 --> 01:19:56.237
It will come tomorrow. I'm sure.

01:19:56.404 --> 01:19:59.949
Well, I'm sure it will, too. Let's go.

01:20:01.034 --> 01:20:03.369
Let's hope so, for your sake, anyway.

01:20:35.026 --> 01:20:37.195
Are you feeling better?

01:20:37.320 --> 01:20:39.530
Yeah, enough to move around. Thanks.

01:20:49.457 --> 01:20:51.334
My hobby.

01:20:52.460 --> 01:20:54.337
One grows old.

01:20:56.089 --> 01:20:57.965
I knew a lot of fellas, friends of mine,

01:20:58.091 --> 01:20:59.967
they just wanted to live to open a bar.

01:21:00.051 --> 01:21:02.512
Had they lived,
would they have done it?

01:21:05.682 --> 01:21:08.851
- Then they were spared their disillusion.
- Yeah, that's right.

01:21:10.895 --> 01:21:13.064
Who were these people?
Friends of yours?

01:21:15.900 --> 01:21:18.986
- I wouldn't hurt a friend.
- Was that my question?

01:21:20.488 --> 01:21:21.823
That's right.

01:21:27.328 --> 01:21:30.707
Well, who are you?

01:21:32.333 --> 01:21:35.837
A fella like you,
trying to make it to retirement.

01:21:35.962 --> 01:21:40.049
At the end of the day, we're likely
to be punished for our kindnesses.

01:21:40.133 --> 01:21:43.177
You don't have to worry about me.
I won't hurt you.

01:22:11.080 --> 01:22:13.374
The 47 ronin, do you know it?

01:22:15.376 --> 01:22:20.882
47 samurai whose master
was betrayed and killed by another lord.

01:22:20.965 --> 01:22:24.510
They became ronin, masterless samurai,

01:22:24.635 --> 01:22:26.846
disgraced by another man's treachery.

01:22:28.306 --> 01:22:30.850
For three years they plotted,
pretending to be thieves,

01:22:31.017 --> 01:22:33.728
mercenaries, even madmen.

01:22:33.853 --> 01:22:36.230
That I didn't have time to do.

01:22:36.314 --> 01:22:38.691
And then one night they struck,
slipping into the castle

01:22:38.858 --> 01:22:40.818
of their lord's betrayer, killing him.

01:22:42.278 --> 01:22:44.739
Nice. I like that. My kind of job.

01:22:44.864 --> 01:22:46.824
There's something more.

01:22:48.409 --> 01:22:52.538
All 47 of them committed seppuku,

01:22:52.663 --> 01:22:56.000
ritual suicide,
in the courtyard of the castle.

01:22:56.125 --> 01:22:58.920
Well, that I don't like so much.

01:22:59.045 --> 01:23:02.173
- But you understand it?
- What do you mean, I understand it?

01:23:04.217 --> 01:23:08.888
The warrior code, the delight in the battle.
You understand that, yes?

01:23:10.139 --> 01:23:13.059
But also something more.

01:23:13.142 --> 01:23:15.520
You understand there is something
outside yourself

01:23:15.645 --> 01:23:18.022
that has to be served.

01:23:18.147 --> 01:23:20.400
And when that need is gone,

01:23:20.525 --> 01:23:23.945
when belief has died, what are you?

01:23:24.028 --> 01:23:26.030
A man without a master.

01:23:26.197 --> 01:23:29.033
Right now I'm a man
without a pay cheque.

01:23:29.158 --> 01:23:32.912
The ronin could have hired
themselves to new masters.

01:23:32.995 --> 01:23:35.164
They could have fought
for themselves.

01:23:35.289 --> 01:23:38.292
But they chose honour.
They chose myth.

01:23:39.460 --> 01:23:41.295
They chose wrong.

01:23:49.095 --> 01:23:51.639
Seppu... Seppu... what?

01:23:51.764 --> 01:23:53.975
Yes, seppuku.

01:23:54.058 --> 01:23:56.310
Disembowelment.

01:23:56.436 --> 01:23:59.188
The sword goes in here.

01:24:09.282 --> 01:24:11.325
Are you sure this address is good?

01:24:11.451 --> 01:24:13.369
Jean-Pierre gave it to me.

01:24:46.819 --> 01:24:50.323
Under the bridge by the river...

01:24:50.406 --> 01:24:53.076
How did you know
it was an ambush?

01:24:53.201 --> 01:24:55.661
Whenever there is any doubt,
there is no doubt.

01:24:55.787 --> 01:24:57.663
That's the first thing they teach you.

01:25:01.417 --> 01:25:04.128
Who taught you?

01:25:04.253 --> 01:25:07.423
I don't remember.
That's the second thing they teach you.

01:25:12.595 --> 01:25:14.889
All good things
come to those who wait.

01:25:45.670 --> 01:25:49.298
- Why is Gregor still alive?
- He's taking them to the package.

01:26:13.865 --> 01:26:15.033
How ya doin'?

01:26:22.915 --> 01:26:25.668
What are you...
What are you gonna do to me?

01:26:25.793 --> 01:26:31.049
Let's just be calm for one more moment.
One more moment.

01:26:43.728 --> 01:26:45.813
Why? Why?

01:26:45.897 --> 01:26:47.982
You know why.

01:26:48.066 --> 01:26:50.234
No. You don't wanna do that.

01:26:54.030 --> 01:26:55.031
You can't.

01:26:59.952 --> 01:27:00.620
Get back!

01:27:02.205 --> 01:27:04.207
Get in the fucking car!

01:27:14.133 --> 01:27:15.718
Why didn't you shoot her?

01:28:07.895 --> 01:28:09.647
Take the tunnel, now!

01:28:09.731 --> 01:28:11.733
Oh, Christ!

01:28:14.027 --> 01:28:16.154
Eh, merde!

01:31:24.634 --> 01:31:26.010
Come on! Come on!

01:31:51.119 --> 01:31:53.079
All right, you fuck!

01:35:20.078 --> 01:35:22.455
Where could he be?

01:35:22.538 --> 01:35:26.501
- Where could he be?
- Hmm.

01:35:26.626 --> 01:35:30.088
The Irish and the Russians are looking
for him. So where does he go?

01:35:30.171 --> 01:35:34.008
He goes to the Russians
to make the deal for the case.

01:35:34.133 --> 01:35:37.637
Gregor ain't comin' in unless
he can figure out a safe exchange.

01:35:37.762 --> 01:35:39.931
He knows they'll kill him for the case
rather than pay him for it.

01:35:40.014 --> 01:35:45.395
He's got to work it out soon
before the Irish find him.

01:35:46.729 --> 01:35:48.564
So where does he go?

01:35:50.400 --> 01:35:52.276
You go to what you know.

01:35:55.822 --> 01:35:59.659
He's KGB.
He goes to one of his old safe houses.

01:36:01.119 --> 01:36:03.746
No, they're all blown.

01:36:03.871 --> 01:36:06.249
Where does he go?

01:36:12.005 --> 01:36:15.425
So, you're on the run.
Where do you go?

01:36:15.550 --> 01:36:17.468
Hmm?

01:36:21.597 --> 01:36:26.019
Where's he been? Where's he been?
Where's he been? Where's he been?

01:36:37.780 --> 01:36:40.324
He made the fake case.

01:36:40.450 --> 01:36:42.827
He had the fake case made.

01:36:42.952 --> 01:36:46.414
Gregor. He had it made.

01:36:46.497 --> 01:36:49.083
He had to have had it made.

01:36:50.585 --> 01:36:53.713
In Paris, before we went to Nice.

01:36:53.796 --> 01:36:55.631
He didn't have time to have it made.

01:36:55.715 --> 01:36:57.925
He bought something that looked like it,
then spray-painted it.

01:36:58.009 --> 01:37:00.595
Where did he get the spray?
He never left the room.

01:37:00.678 --> 01:37:02.680
Where did he get the case?

01:37:12.315 --> 01:37:14.567
Excusez-moi, monsieur.

01:37:35.880 --> 01:37:37.715
It's a case for ice skates.

01:37:41.302 --> 01:37:43.221
Why ice skates?

01:37:45.515 --> 01:37:47.517
And why would Gregor
know an ice-skate case?

01:37:49.519 --> 01:37:51.979
He didn't have time to have it made.

01:37:52.146 --> 01:37:56.943
He didn't have time to have it made.
The Russians made it.

01:37:58.903 --> 01:38:01.489
The Russians made it.

01:38:04.617 --> 01:38:06.494
We're following the wrong people.

01:38:06.619 --> 01:38:09.539
We don't have to find Gregor.

01:38:09.664 --> 01:38:12.375
We find the Russians,
they will take us to him.

01:38:12.500 --> 01:38:16.337
You've lived in Paris
a long time. You know the people.

01:38:16.462 --> 01:38:19.507
- I get around.
- You meet the new Russians.

01:38:19.590 --> 01:38:23.511
You know how it is.
Ex-spies. Now it's Mafia.

01:38:24.387 --> 01:38:26.514
Under diplomatic cover.

01:38:28.057 --> 01:38:29.058
KGB?

01:38:29.308 --> 01:38:30.309
Ex-KGB.

01:38:30.727 --> 01:38:35.314
Heavy hitters, gamblers,
lots ofmoney, big cars.

01:38:35.398 --> 01:38:36.816
They live like tsars.
Throw money away.

01:38:36.899 --> 01:38:38.776
Fur hats are expensive.

01:38:38.860 --> 01:38:44.282
- And bodyguards.
- Expensive coats, Dr Zhivago.

01:38:44.365 --> 01:38:47.535
I have a lot of work, no time.

01:38:49.037 --> 01:38:50.663
I understand.

01:38:52.415 --> 01:38:54.125
All right. Let's go.

01:38:55.043 --> 01:38:56.044
Okay.

01:39:03.217 --> 01:39:04.802
It will be fine.

01:39:06.304 --> 01:39:08.181
The guy is gonna reach out.

01:39:08.264 --> 01:39:10.183
Is he any good?

01:39:10.308 --> 01:39:13.186
Jean-Pierre says if it's Russian
and it's in Paris...

01:39:24.280 --> 01:39:27.700
Ifl wanted to find Russians
in Paris this week,

01:39:27.784 --> 01:39:31.954
I'd go to the ice show.

01:40:45.987 --> 01:40:48.114
- Bonsoir, Pierre.
- Bonsoir.

01:40:48.197 --> 01:40:50.116
Je vais payer pour votre soeur.

01:40:50.199 --> 01:40:53.578
Oh, merci beaucoup,
Mademoiselle Kirilova.

01:41:00.084 --> 01:41:04.839
I'll trade you a cigarette for a favour.

01:41:05.381 --> 01:41:07.300
The favour is, steer clear of those guys.

01:41:07.383 --> 01:41:08.885
Who? The Russians?

01:41:15.391 --> 01:41:17.602
They sure throw their money around.

01:41:18.728 --> 01:41:19.812
Bonsoir.

01:41:19.896 --> 01:41:22.106
- Ça va? - Salut.

01:41:25.401 --> 01:41:27.278
- Bonsoir.
- Ah, bonsoir.

01:41:33.826 --> 01:41:38.164
The Russian is seeing Natacha Kirilova,
the star of the ice show.

01:41:38.247 --> 01:41:41.834
He spends every evening in the audience.

01:41:43.086 --> 01:41:44.587
How did you find that out?

01:41:44.671 --> 01:41:47.965
We went to high school together.

01:42:22.208 --> 01:42:24.669
Mikhi, is everything all right?

01:42:25.461 --> 01:42:26.879
Everything is fine.

01:42:28.089 --> 01:42:29.090
Sweet girl.

01:42:31.926 --> 01:42:32.927
Go. Go on.

01:42:51.904 --> 01:42:53.656
Ladies and gentlemen!

01:42:53.740 --> 01:42:57.035
We are veryproud to present...

01:42:57.118 --> 01:43:04.000
...two-time Olympic champion
and three-time World champion...

01:43:04.083 --> 01:43:07.712
...Natacha Kirilova!

01:45:14.005 --> 01:45:15.923
Let's go.

01:45:29.270 --> 01:45:31.397
Wait out here.

01:45:36.361 --> 01:45:38.613
Yes, he is.

01:45:38.696 --> 01:45:40.782
Hello, Mikhi.

01:45:40.907 --> 01:45:44.911
- The meeting is not till later tonight.
- The meeting's now.

01:45:48.289 --> 01:45:49.874
You have the money?

01:45:51.209 --> 01:45:55.129
Well, we were going to go back
to get it before the meet.

01:45:55.213 --> 01:45:56.297
I don't think so.

01:45:57.799 --> 01:45:59.717
You have the money?

01:46:04.138 --> 01:46:07.141
I might have the money.
Where is the case?

01:46:07.225 --> 01:46:11.604
No, you have to do it.
I couldn't live with myself.

01:46:24.575 --> 01:46:26.452
I have the money.

01:46:26.577 --> 01:46:29.080
We conclude this now
and part friends.

01:46:29.163 --> 01:46:30.957
Okay?

01:46:33.835 --> 01:46:34.919
Where is the case?

01:46:47.306 --> 01:46:49.183
I'd like to be paid now.

01:46:54.772 --> 01:46:56.941
No doubt.

01:47:01.696 --> 01:47:03.573
Now tell me the other part.

01:47:05.033 --> 01:47:07.201
The other part?

01:47:07.327 --> 01:47:09.203
I'm leaving.

01:47:09.329 --> 01:47:12.206
I'm taking my fee and I'm leaving.

01:47:13.833 --> 01:47:16.919
I have a person with a rifle in the stadium.

01:47:17.128 --> 01:47:19.964
I've worked with her for years.
She never misses.

01:47:20.089 --> 01:47:23.051
I will call.

01:47:23.176 --> 01:47:25.511
I have to call within 45 seconds

01:47:25.636 --> 01:47:27.722
to say that I'm leaving,

01:47:27.847 --> 01:47:31.017
and then in another 10 minutes
to say that I'm safe.

01:47:32.685 --> 01:47:36.606
Should I be unable to call,
your friend will be shot.

01:47:46.449 --> 01:47:48.326
30 seconds, Mikhi.

01:47:49.744 --> 01:47:52.246
- We need to get inside.
- You can'tpass without badges.

01:47:59.587 --> 01:48:01.422
20 seconds.

01:48:12.100 --> 01:48:13.101
10 seconds.

01:48:42.338 --> 01:48:45.216
There were two of them.

01:48:45.299 --> 01:48:47.010
They were looking for those guys.

01:48:47.093 --> 01:48:49.262
Just a minute, sir!

01:49:05.820 --> 01:49:09.741
I am a Chilean citizen,
as you can see from mypassport.

01:49:09.824 --> 01:49:11.492
Merci.

01:49:49.947 --> 01:49:53.117
- Mama!
- Shh, shh, shh.

01:49:58.956 --> 01:50:00.583
Katchev!

01:50:00.667 --> 01:50:01.834
Qu'est-ce qui se passe?

01:50:16.849 --> 01:50:17.850
Stay with him.

01:50:50.717 --> 01:50:53.261
Get out of here.
Get out of here!

01:50:53.386 --> 01:50:56.222
Get out of the car.
Walk away. Walk away!

01:50:56.305 --> 01:50:59.142
Walk away! Go. Go.

01:50:59.225 --> 01:51:02.103
- I will if you will.
- Just go.

01:51:02.186 --> 01:51:04.647
Come with me.
Forget about the case.

01:51:09.068 --> 01:51:11.529
I didn't come for the case.
I came for your boss.

01:51:13.406 --> 01:51:15.950
I came for Seamus. I came for him.

01:51:17.368 --> 01:51:22.290
Just get out of here.
I never left. Don't you see?

01:51:23.666 --> 01:51:26.002
Get out of the way!
Get out of the way!

01:51:34.344 --> 01:51:35.678
Get out of the way!

01:51:35.762 --> 01:51:37.096
This way is blocked.

01:52:04.916 --> 01:52:06.793
I can take you in or leave you here.

01:52:08.294 --> 01:52:09.545
There. That's him with the case.

01:52:09.629 --> 01:52:11.756
Sir! Over here, please.

01:52:11.839 --> 01:52:12.590
Wait! Wait!

01:52:20.223 --> 01:52:23.267
There are more back there!

01:53:00.555 --> 01:53:02.432
Stay where you are!
Stay where you are!

01:53:02.515 --> 01:53:06.394
Don't move! Shut your fuckin' mouth up!
Shut your mouth!

01:53:20.408 --> 01:53:22.243
You stupid shite.

01:53:22.410 --> 01:53:25.955
You're a dead man.

01:53:48.478 --> 01:53:50.855
This is the BBC World Service.

01:53:50.980 --> 01:53:53.649
It was announced today,
after almost 30 years

01:53:53.775 --> 01:53:57.153
ofbloody and seemingly intractable
civil conflict in Northern Ireland,

01:53:57.236 --> 01:53:59.155
that a peace agreement
has been reached between

01:53:59.280 --> 01:54:02.492
the predominantly Protestant
government of that British-ruled enclave,

01:54:02.617 --> 01:54:05.161
and the Irish resistance...

01:54:09.957 --> 01:54:13.544
...have told CNN that it was
the apprehension and slaying

01:54:13.670 --> 01:54:18.508
in France of the Irish terrorist Seamus
O'Rourke, byparties still unknown,

01:54:18.591 --> 01:54:20.927
that contributed a stability,
largely allowing

01:54:21.010 --> 01:54:25.014
the negotiations to proceed
to their historic conclusion today.

01:54:25.139 --> 01:54:28.059
O'Rourke had earlier
been denounced by the IRA,

01:54:28.184 --> 01:54:32.271
the military wing ofSinn Fein,
as a rogue breakaway operative.

01:54:34.774 --> 01:54:38.111
Well, then, good knowin' ya.

01:54:48.830 --> 01:54:49.831
Hmm?

01:54:49.914 --> 01:54:53.126
- I'm sorry?
- You said something.

01:54:53.209 --> 01:54:56.713
I said she would not
be coming back here.

01:54:58.881 --> 01:55:03.344
Yeah. She would
not be coming back here, would she?

01:55:09.600 --> 01:55:11.686
I can't even put my hand in my pocket
to pay the bill.

01:55:11.769 --> 01:55:13.938
I'll get it.

01:55:16.441 --> 01:55:18.276
I'll get the next one.

01:55:24.615 --> 01:55:26.367
What was in the case?

01:55:26.576 --> 01:55:28.619
I don't remember.

